    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>The spread of COVID-19 epidemic in some highly-impacted Indian states displayed a characteristic sub-exponential growth projected up to 3 May 2020, as a consequence of lockdown strategies, in addition to improvement of reproduction number (R), serial interval, and daily growth rate, but not case fatality rate (CFR). The effect of COVID-19 containment was more prominent in second phase of lockdown with declining R, which was still &gt;1, suggesting the requirement of sustained interventions for effective containment of COVID-19 pandemic in Indian context.</jats:p>",
